===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|da|en}} {{m|da|gibbe||jib, jibe}}, related to Swedish {{m|sv|gippa||jib, jibe, jerk, make jump}}, Dutch {{m|nl|gijpen}} {{gloss|"to turn sails suddenly"; > English {{m|en|jibe}}}}. Compare also Middle High German {{m|gmh|gempeln||to spring}}, Swedish {{m|sv|guppa||to move up and down}}, Swedish {{m|sv|gumpa||to jump, spring}}. See {{l/en|jump}}.
